---
title: Privacy Policy
---

%main.prose
  %h1 Privacy Policy

  %p.effective-date Effective: June 2025

  %p
    Aroid is a podcast player. It fetches podcast feeds and plays audio.
    It does not have accounts, does not track you, and does not sell data.
    This policy describes the limited data that does leave your device and why.

  %h2 What leaves your device

  %h3 Podcast feed requests
  %p
    When you subscribe to a podcast or refresh your library, the app fetches
    RSS feeds directly from the podcast publishers you choose to follow. Those
    servers receive your IP address and a standard HTTP user-agent string,
    exactly as any podcast app or web browser does. Aroid has no control over
    how podcast publishers handle these requests.

  %h3 iTunes Search API
  %p
    When you search for a podcast to add, your search query is sent to
    Apple's iTunes Search API. Apple's
    %a{href: 'https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/'} privacy policy
    governs that request.

  %h3 Crash reports
  %p
    If the app crashes, a diagnostic report is sent to
    %a{href: 'https://sentry.io'} Sentry,
    a crash-reporting service. These reports contain a crash stack trace
    and basic technical device information (OS version, app version, device
    model). They do not contain your podcast subscriptions, episode content,
    transcripts, or any information that identifies you as an individual.
    Sentry's servers are located in the United States.

  %h2 What stays on your device

  %ul
    %li
      %strong Subscriptions and episode metadata
      — feed URLs, episode titles, descriptions, and publication dates are
      stored in a local database and never transmitted.
    %li
      %strong Playback state
      — your listening position and history are stored locally and excluded
      from iCloud backup.
    %li
      %strong Downloaded audio
      — episode files you download are stored on your device and excluded
      from iCloud backup.
    %li
      %strong Transcripts, chapters, and audio analysis
      — all on-device processing (transcription, speaker diarization, and
      audio analysis) runs entirely on your device using on-device models.
      No audio or transcript content is ever sent to a server.

  %h2 iCloud settings sync

  %p
    App preferences (playback speed, skip intervals, refresh frequency, and
    similar settings) may be synced across your devices via iCloud. This sync
    contains only your in-app configuration — no podcast subscriptions, episode
    content, or listening history. iCloud sync is governed by
    %a{href: 'https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/'} Apple's privacy policy.

  %h2 Changes to this policy

  %p
    If this policy changes materially, the effective date above will be updated.
    Continued use of the app after a change constitutes acceptance of the
    updated policy.

  %h2 Contact

  %p
    Questions about this policy:
    %a{href: 'mailto:contact@aroidpod.com'} contact@aroidpod.com
